messages.content: Which version of ComfyUI does cgem156-ComfyUI support?
cgem156-ComfyUI only supports version 3 of ComfyUI.
What is required for cgem156-ComfyUI to work?
cgem156-ComfyUI requires timm (a Python library) to function properly.
Who created the recommended node for use with cgem156-ComfyUI?
The recommended node for use with cgem156-ComfyUI was created by pythongosssss.
Where can the recommended node for cgem156-ComfyUI be found?
The recommended node for cgem156-ComfyUI can be found at https://github.com/pythongosssss/ComfyUI-WD14-Tagger.
Is cgem156-ComfyUI compatible with versions other than v3?
No, cgem156-ComfyUI is only compatible with version 3 of ComfyUI.
What is the purpose of the image included in the documentation?
The image included in the documentation visually represents the cgem156-ComfyUI and its functionality.
Is timm an optional or required dependency for cgem156-ComfyUI?
Timm is a required dependency for cgem156-ComfyUI to function properly.
